README for lojeme
================================================================================
Description

This is a framework to enable object oriented programming in Prolog. The focus
is on fast execution time and ease of use. Objects are implemented in a
parametric style. Currently only SWI Prolog is supported.

lojeme is
LOgic
obJEct
paraMEtrics

================================================================================
Try It Out

> cd example/shape
> swipl

?- [load].
%  library(lojeme) compiled 0.00 sec, 15,960 bytes
%  line_segment compiled 0.02 sec, 468,792 bytes
%  square compiled 0.01 sec, 4,416 bytes
%  cube compiled 0.00 sec, 4,144 bytes
% load compiled 0.03 sec, 496,592 bytes
true.

?- square.new(S, 10, red), S.color(Color), S.area(Area).
S = square(line_segment(10, red), red),
Color = red,
Area = 100 .

?- cube.new(C, 10), C.set_color(green), C.area(Area).
C = cube(line_segment(10, _G21), green),
Area = 1000 .

================================================================================
Status

This project is currently EXPERIMENTAL, many things may change in future
updates.

